OL,4,CWomen taken from Congo sue Belgium over
OL,5,Cforced separations
OL,6, Five women who were born in Congo and
OL,7, separated from their mothers by the
OL,8, colonial authorities are suing Belgium
OL,9, for crimes against humanity.
OL,11,FThe mixed-race women were taken away
OL,12,Ffrom their black mothers at birth 70
OL,13,Fyears ago solely on the basis of the
OL,14,Fcolour of their skin.
OL,16,FBelgium controlled the central African
OL,17,Fcountry from the 19th Century until it
OL,18,Fwon its independence in 1960.
OL,20,FMillions of Africans died during
OL,21,Fcolonial rule.
